body.description: Tissues may be soft, but there’s only one Kleenex Ultra Soft—made with three thick layers for a perfect balance of softness and strength. Whether it's for cold and flu season, pollen allergies, or everything in between you'll have plenty for everyone with Kleenex Ultra Soft with 4 cube boxes of 60 ultra soft tissues. Designed for runny noses and watery eyes, our lotion-free and dye-free tissues have no added fragrance and feature soft, strong and absorbent care for face and hands. Plus, you can find a tissue box that’s attractive for your home in various colors and designs. 100% of our pulp is from responsibly managed forests. Want to nourish your skin? Try Kleenex Soothing Lotion Facial Tissues with Coconut Oil, Aloe and Vitamin E.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am a Kleenex brand tissue user only. I purchased these from Amazon when my local retailers had been out for quite a bit longer than was convenient. What I really like about this particular iteration of Kleenex products is that they are soft they are sturdy, and very absorbent. But perhaps, the best quality of all is that they don’t shred into little tiny pieces when you forget you had one in your pocket and it goes through the wash. Yes, you will be removing pieces of tissue from your clothes, but they are large pieces, and easy to just pull off and throw away. One thing that I don’t like, and it’s a total personal preference, is the new design on the boxes. They are very cutesy, and tropical, with bright colors, and birds and flowers, and that is not my aesthetic. And if the last design is any indication, they will keep this one for years. I keep Kleenex boxes in every room of the house, and I would rather have them blend in and be neutral, then be some thing that stands out as a conversation piece. I understand why they don’t, but I definitely wish there were more choices of types of patterns. But you can’t go wrong with Kleenex brand tissues.
